"title": "8255: fruit, spiritual",
"media_type": "Text",
"index_reference": "8255",
"language": "eng",
"review_level": "None",
"content": "<p>The spiritual life and growth of believers is likened to a fruit-bearing tree. As the fruit is evidence of the health and vigour of the tree, so the believer's life, attitudes and behaviour should reflect the presence of the Holy Spirit.</p>\n<h2>Believers should exhibit evidence of their conversion</h2>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Jas3:13\">JAS 3:13</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt3:8\">MAT 3:8</a> parallel <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke3:8-Luke3:9\">LUK 3:8–3:9</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt7:15-Matt7:20\">MAT 7:15–7:20</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt12:33\">MAT 12:33</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/John15:16\">JHN 15:16</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rom7:4-Rom7:5\">ROM 7:4–7:5</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Titus3:14\">TIT 3:14</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Jas2:14-Jas2:26\">JAS 2:14–2:26</a></p>\n<h2>The nature of spiritual fruit</h2>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Gal5:22-Gal5:23\">GAL 5:22–5:23</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rom8:5-Rom8:6\">ROM 8:5–8:6</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Phil1:9-Phil1:11\">PHP 1:9–1:11</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Jas3:17\">JAS 3:17</a></p>\n<h2>The sources of spiritual fruit</h2>\n<h3>Acceptance of the gospel</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke8:15\">LUK 8:15</a></strong> parallels <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt13:23\">MAT 13:23</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Mark4:20\">MRK 4:20</a></p>\n<h3>The old way of life put to death</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/John12:24\">JHN 12:24</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rom6:6\">ROM 6:6</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rom6:11-Rom6:14\">ROM 6:11–6:14</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rom8:13-Rom8:14\">ROM 8:13–8:14</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Gal5:24\">GAL 5:24</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Eph4:22-Eph4:24\">EPH 4:22–4:24</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Col3:5-Col3:10\">COL 3:5–3:10</a></p>\n<h3>Actively living a new life in Jesus Christ</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Gal6:7-Gal6:9\">GAL 6:7–6:9</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rom6:11-Rom6:14\">ROM 6:11–6:14</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Gal5:25\">GAL 5:25</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Eph5:8-Eph5:9\">EPH 5:8–5:9</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Col1:10\">COL 1:10</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Col3:12-Col3:15\">COL 3:12–3:15</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Tim2:22\">2TI 2:22</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Pet1:5-2Pet1:8\">2PE 1:5–1:8</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Titus3:14\">TIT 3:14</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1John3:18\">1JN 3:18</a></p>\n<h3>Remaining close to Jesus Christ</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/John15:4-John15:5\">JHN 15:4–15:5</a></strong></p>\n<h3>Submission to God's discipline</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Heb12:10-Heb12:11\">HEB 12:10–12:11</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/John15:1-John15:2\">JHN 15:1–15:2</a></p>",
